Ealan, people welcome these changes with open arms. Why, because they’re all(yes, all) positive changes to the game play, classes and overall game. As a matter of fact, I didn’t see one negative change mentioned in that whole post. Why, because Verant would be shooting themselves in the foot if they nerf’d anything at this point, there’s going to be competition to soak up the pissed off people unlike when they assaulted Necros with the Nerfbat™ and shoved it up the ass of high-level Clerics.<br>
<br>
Think about history, and what games actually threatened Verant’s market, even a little. I can only think of a few, like Diablo 2. Everyone was psyched for this game(even though we all knew it would be more of the same) and Verant knew it. There was nothing but positive changes to Everquest for the month before and after the release of Diablo 2. Verant felt the affects of that game’s introduction, for a month Emarr dropped from 1800 people to 1400 until they slowly trickled back.<br>
<br>
Verant has a list of everything you and me have ever asked for. It’s in a glass cabinet on the wall marked, “in case of competition, break glass!” They know everything that needs to be done, they know everything that the vast majority want done. They only choose to implement these changes if/when something arises to threaten their market.<br>
<br>
FoH pointed out how shitty ToV weapons were, what, 3 months ago?<br>
Didn’t we ask for horses, like, 18 months ago?<br>
Hasn’t warrior taunt been, basically, ineffective since the release of Kunark?<br>
How are Casters having a problem with high-end encounters a new issue?<br>
Chardok is just recently devoid of people? <p><b>Vendrix</b><br>
