<br>
Yes they are making changes. They have made changes good and bad since the beginning.<br>
<br>
To put it simply I believe that if someone walked up to these people and said &quot;Hey i'm going to give you a million dollars&quot; their response would be &quot;Why didn't you give it to me last month when I needed it?&quot;<br>
<br>
Simply put if this is such a screwed up game then don't play it. Hell it is the only game that has kept my interest for an extended period of time. No other game could do that and definately not on the same scale. They can't make everyone happy and no matter what they do someone is gonna bitch.<br>
<br>
So if you don't like what they are doing or how good or bad their customer service is then STFU and go play another game.<br>
However if you like the game and what they have done and just feel a change here or there would help then give them positive feed back and hope for the best. I to date have not seen a game which comes close to what Everquest has accomplished.<br>
